        "caption": "Photo credit: Speed Digital"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If you aren’t that familiar with the trend of airbrushing rust, faded paint spots, and other “imperfections” on a freshly-repainted vehicle, you might at first be fooled into thinking this Chevy wears its original paint. They chose a color which looks vintage enough, but the fact there’s a clearcoat over the discolored areas is the dead giveaway. The virtually perfect chrome isn’t, because some people will keep a weathered body untouched on a classic while dressing up the trim – a trend that yet again doesn’t please everyone.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/07/1957-chevrolet-31003.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "Photo credit: Speed Digital"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Many people judge an old truck by its bed, and this one really shines in that area, literally. Fresh oak has been stained lightly enough to let that woodgrain peek through. Stainless steel strips dress up the space further, so you won’t want to throw landscaping rock or sod back there.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/07/1957-chevrolet-31004.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "Photo credit: Speed Digital"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The paint, chrome, and payload aren’t everything fresh on this truck. A 350ci V8 crate engine has been installed with an Edelbrock Intake and carb. Other modern touches include four-wheel disc brakes, power steering, and a Ridetech air suspension. Up front is a Mustang II suspension with the promise the pickup has a sportier feel.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "caption": "Photo credit: Speed Digital",
